      "body" : "@jonasschnelli You can represent every *valid* amount of bitcoins as a double. In case the exact representation is not possible, you can get back the original amount by rounding. There will never be an issue up to 21e6. I think the first off-by-one satoshi rounding error is somewhere in the order of 60e6.\r\n\r\nI see no reason to drop support for floating point. Especially given that the documentation indicates that rounding was intended and probably working in earlier versions of core. Can someone test this with 0.9, etc?",
